headline: WWE fans forced to switch platforms after major Netflix change
summary: In 2024, Netflix raised eyebrows when it secured one of the biggest shows in sports entertainment. In January of that year, the streaming giant announced in a press release a $5 billion 10-year deal with WWE (owned by TKO), making Netflix the new home of WWE’s “Monday Night Raw” after the ...
